<br>
And the end of this, when chanters are so greedy that they won't even give a KEI out on a raid that they are a part of, there's a problem.  And yes, this happened to me recently on a Kith raid that I organized to help the chanter's buddy on.  No, I get told that she only casts KEI on people that can afford her 100pp charge.  And that was after a 56 cleric rezzed an entire Naggy raid for free, for those of you that want to cleric bash.  I don't think I've ever seen a cleric make 10kpp on rezzes in 3 hours, and if I did, I'd be the first to slap the greedy prick.  No one has EVER been as miserly and greedy as the enchanter community with a NO REAGENT spell!  Come on, you guys make up Shaka's 30kpp or even the EXTREMELY inflated 60kpp in a matter of days.  Sounds to me like you're doing much better than the rest of us who will NEVER make up the cost of our upper end spells.  For a group of people who's response to me is &quot;Quit whining...stand in line and take up the arse like the other casters&quot;  You seem to be making a point of whining about that price you paid for this spell that has you banking in the dough.  Guess what, there'll be another expansion eventually, Verant love that money just as much as you do, and don't be surprised to find yourself on the arse end of the class balancing stick.  God willing the rumors of a KEI nerf I keep hearing are true.  So suck it up while you can, but remember, every class get their 5 minutes of fame, and when it's over everyone still remembers whether you acted with honor and integrity, or how you acted to take advantage of others.  Personally, I don't care whether I have or don't have KEI, a cleric is always taken over a chanter because at the end of the day, we save lives.  And to those chanters out there that want to spend your time fleecing the populace because taking meager donations have only made you a meager 25 thousand platinum, enjoy it while it lasts.  But remember, every dog has his day, and that doesn't just apply to druids =).<br>
